1 23–201.
2 (a) The Central Library of the Enoch Pratt Free Library System is the State
3 Library Resource Center.
4 (b) The State Library Resource Center shall provide and expand access to
5 specialized library materials and services that are necessary for coordinated, efficient, and
6 economical library services in this State.
7 23–205.
8 (c) (1) Subject to subsection (g) of this section, each year each participating
9 regional resource center shall receive a minimum amount of funding for each resident of
10 the area served, to be used for operating and capital expenses.
11 (2) The allocation shall be calculated as follows:
12 (i) [For each of fiscal years 2011 through 2015... $6.75 per each
13 resident of the area served;
14 (ii) For fiscal year 2016............................................ $6.95 per each
15 resident of the area served;
16 (iii) For fiscal year 2017............................................ $7.15 per each
17 resident of the area served;
18 (iv) For fiscal year 2018............................................ $7.55 per each
19 resident of the area served;
